 of integration in the plural, both in its multiple histories and in the many possible definitions of and courses of action for integration. Ultimately, the authors show, integration cannot guarantee educational equality and justice, but it is an essential component of civic education that prepares students for life in our multiracial democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEducational equalizationxPhilosophy. 0aEducational equalizationzUnited States. 0aEducational equalization-Philosophy. 0aEducational equalization-United States. 0aMinoritiesxEducationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMinorities-Education-United States-History. 0aRacism in educationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRacism in educationzUnited States. 0aRacism in education-United States-History. 0aRacism in education-United States. 0aSchool integrationzUnited States. 0aSchool integration-United States. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aintegration, segregation, white supremacy, educational equality, race and class, African Americans, Latinxs, Indigenous peoples, Asian Americans, racial equality.1 aBurkholder, Zoë, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishz978311075406308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2021z9783110753950oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226786179423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/is